However, 4 points in general position (not necessarily in arithmetic progression) may not immediately form a triple. So, we need a more careful argument.

Alternatively, we can use the fact that if we have 8 points, then there must be some structure. For example, if we have 4 points of the same color, then there must be a pair of pairs with the same difference, which would form a triple.

